Across the water from the permanent home of Boao Forum for Asia (BFA), the Courtyard of Eastern Culture is located in Boao Water Town and its total floor area reaches 60,000 square meters. Consisting of Boao Temple, Wanfo Pagoda and water sightseeing area, the courtyard is regarded as the cultural symbol of Boao. Visitors can choose different green vehicles to arrive at the courtyard. Qionghai—Boao Eastern Culture park shuttle bus was officially opened on June 7, 2007, the shuttle bus runs every 8 minutes, the terminus of the line is located in the Courtyard of Eastern Culture scenery area. Apart from shuttle bus, visitors can take new energy vehicles to the courtyard this year as at least 300 new energy vehicles were put into use during the annual BFA conference this year. Read more: Low-carbon travel in Boao: BFA International Convention Center Low-carbon travel in Bo'ao: Yudai Beach